Reference-contexts: Essentially Fitts law states that movement time can be quantified based on an index of difficulty. This index of difficulty (ID) is defined as ID = log 2 (A/W + 1) (1) where A is the distance or amplitude to move and W is the width of the target <ref> [6] </ref>. This formula is a refinement from the original equation for ID since this new formulation provides a slightly better fit with given data, it exactly mimics the information theorem that is the basis of Fitts law, and it always gives a positive rating for the ID [7].
