Reference-contexts: This formula is a refinement from the original equation for ID since this new formulation provides a slightly better fit with given data, it exactly mimics the information theorem that is the basis of Fitts law, and it always gives a positive rating for the ID <ref> [7] </ref>. So using equation 1, Fitts law states that MT = a + b (ID) (2) MT = b (ID) (3) where MT equals movement time, and a and b are the intercept and slope coefficients respectively.
